history.content: Depends on what side of CS you're most interested in and what career path you see for yourself. I would say CS 189 and CS 186 would be most useful because Data 100 (which I took last semester) is more focused on data science, specific Python packages to perform data analysis, and stats / data analysis-focused projects like Trump tweet sentiment analysis, etc. If you already know how to use Pandas, NumPy, scikit-learn you might not learn too much from the class because it doesn't go very deep into the math behind the ml functions we call. However, 186 and 189 might be too hard together along with a math class while Data 100 is comparatively conceptually and workload-wise light. I personally would recommend 186 and 100 if you're interested in more swe roles, and 189 and 100 if you're more ml-focused.

So I plan to take a math course but I wanna take a couple of these courses, which two of these three would be the best in terms of managebilility and usefulness?

Data 100
CS 189
CS186

Thanks!
